metadata.name: Colorfall #40
metadata.description:
My first attempt at a generative NFT. This started with an idea to create a grid of diagonal lines with the basic line function of p5js. I had discarded this idea until my friend said it looked like a waterfall of colors and he liked it, so I decided to mint it. After tweaking some parameters like colors and line thickness it produced some nice outputs.

I hope you will enjoy it. Free mint(unless you cant wait and want to pay =) plus 25% royalties for minters.

reserves for the collectors of my testnft on objkt, my friend CampendonkP and a few artists who I remembered who did free mints, like punevyr and JohnRising.

metadata.name: Mooving Squigly #130
metadata.description:
A mooving squigly generator inspirated by "Chromie Squiggle by snowfro"
@ArtOnBlockchain on twitter
Made using p5.js

This project aim to be your unique mooving web3 signature

The features define the visual of your squigly
DIFFERENT FEATURES :

    Background Color: #7AA5A6, #FBB900, #FCBF49, #FFFFFF, #F5F3EC, #1F1F1F, #F9EBDC, #F0C328, #8AC1CC
    Squigly Color Theme: flash, chromatic, cloud, kaki, darkred
    Stroke: none, max 10
    Squigly Number: 1, 2, 3
    Special Color Mode: true, false
    Squigly Size: medium, small, large, extra large
    Speed: max 5
    Style: classic, expansion, distortion, blur, gray

The colours and positions are calculated using deterministic perlin noise
Press S to save the squigly
Reload the page to see your squigly moove again

Made with <3 by 0xtedy.tez / @0xtedy
All the code is opensource !
MIT License

metadata.name: SQUARE GAMES #58
metadata.description:
Quite frankely: a lot of squares

An exploration of recursion
featuring very vibrant color combinations
Interactive

4 recursion depths
16 color palettes
4 expansion states
4 fill probabilities 
4 ghost probabilities 

Press 's' to save a high res image
Click and move mouse to explore
Press 'space' to return to original position
Press 'b' to change color of white cube
Press ‚f‘ for fullscreen
Press 'p‘ to toggle pixel perfect rendering
